<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-12-05T23:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-12-05T23:00:00-05:00" n="290" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d290">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">722.2315/2633: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Ecuador</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Long</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Quito</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-12-05T23:00:00-05:00">December 5, 1941—11
                                        p.m.</date><lb/>[Received December 5—10:55 p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>496. Department’s telegram 368, December 4, 2 p.m. Doctor Tobar
                                accepts the addition of Chile to the countries which are kindly
                                extending their good offices in the boundary matter.</p>
                            <p>I am led to believe that the suggestion about including Mexico has
                                been withdrawn.</p>
                            <p>Repeated to Lima.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Long</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>